Wash and dry produce.

If desired, peel @potatoes{12%ounce}. Dice potatoes into ½-inch pieces. Place in a
#medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil
and cook until tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid; drain and return potatoes to pot. Keep
covered off heat until ready to mash in Step 4.

While potatoes cook, trim and thinly slice @cremini mushrooms{4%ounce}
(skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Quarter @lemon{1}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Place between two
large pieces of #plastic wrap{}; pound with a #mallet{} or
#heavy-bottomed pan{} until about ½ inch thick. Season all over with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Sprinkle chicken all over with @flour{1%tablespoon}, pressing to adhere; shake
off any excess.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add coated chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes}
per side. (For 4 servings, you may need to cook in batches.) Turn off heat;
transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

Return pot with drained potatoes to low heat. Add half the @sour cream{3%tablespoon},
half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, and @butter{1%tablespoon}. (You'll use the
rest of the sour cream and garlic powder in the next step.)

Mash until smooth and creamy using a #potato masher{}, adding splashes of
reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season with salt and pepper. Keep
covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Creamy Mushroom Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add
mushrooms; season with remaining garlic powder and pepper. Cook, stirring,
until softened, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1} and @water{1/4%cup}. Bring to a boil,
then reduce to a low simmer. Cook, stirring, until slightly thickened,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat. Stir in remaining sour cream and @butter{1%tablespoon} until
melted and combined. Season with salt and pepper.

== Arugula Salad ==

In a #large bowl{}, toss @arugula{2%ounce} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon},
a squeeze of lemon juice, salt, and pepper until evenly coated. Taste and
season with more salt and pepper if desired.

== To Serve ==

Divide chicken, mashed potatoes, and salad between plates.

Spoon mushroom sauce over chicken and mashed potatoes. Sprinkle
@parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon} over salad. Serve with remaining lemon wedges
on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.